The paper deals with the problem of aligning two RDF databases, which is a fundamental problem in understanding the evolution of ontologies. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, given that the paper proposes approaches inspired by graph bisimulation, which is a well-known technique in database theory, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because the paper involves techniques from machine learning, information retrieval, and software engineering.
